The hetras API is using this [Patch Specification](https://developer.hetras.com/docs/patch) to partially update an existing resource. Currently this call only allows to set the base price for non-derived rateplans if the rateplan is active and already loaded for the specified time period.  

A request example:  

            [
              {
                "op": "replace", "path": "/base_price", "value": 120.00
              }
            ]


For more details on how the API responds to errors please check our documentation on [Error Handling](https://developer.hetras.com/docs/errors/).

